children.name: Rules
children.text:
This brightly-colored costume includes a full-face mask, and cannot be worn with armor. In addition, it can only be worn by the person it was designed for. While you are wearing this costume, you gain the following features:
- Your AC is +1. This does not stack with other AC bonuses from magical clothing.
- You can use Dexterity or Intelligence when making an Athletics check to grapple of avoid being grappled.
- While you are grappling a creature, as an attack you can slam them to the ground. They become prone, are no longer grappled, and you deal 1d6+STR modifier bludgeoning damage.
